<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215180>
    bibo:endPage "61" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "52" ;
    bibo:volume "3422" ;
    dc:creator "Turak, Emre; Devantier, Lyndon; Erdmann, Mark" ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "Euphyllia baliensis sp. nov. (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Scleractinia: Euphylliidae): a new species of reef coral from Indonesia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215181>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215182> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215181>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Corallite budding and new branch formation in Euphyllia baliensis sp. nov. a — Corallite elongates and two opposing primary septa on the narrow axis begin to fuse. b — The corallite begins to pinch along the long axis and the upper wall begins to overgrow along the middle of the short axis. c — Walls on the opposing ends fuse forming two daughter corallites. d — Corallites grow apart. e — New independent corallites form new branches. f — Rarely a triple division may occur, which leads to triple branching. Scale—all images 1 cm wide. Photos by E. Turak." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/215181/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215182>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Underwater appearance of Euphyllia baliensis sp. nov. a — Polyps extended, showing tentacle shape and arrangement. b — Polyps and tentacles fully extended in a more sparsely branching colony. c — Comparison of size and tentacle shape with E. glabrescens (top left). d — Polyps retracted showing encrusting epibenthic sponges. Scale bars; 2 cm in a and d, 5 cm in b and c. Photos a and b by E. Turak, c and d by L. DeVantier." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/215182/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

